data.name: toolStripButtonPrevious.ToolTipText
data.value: Loads the previous unlabeled image. The displayed image will be saved in the "Labeled" folder together with label files. Existing image and label files will be overwritten. Hint: it can also be done by using the mouse wheel.

data.name: toolStripButtonNext.ToolTipText
data.value: Loads the next unlabeled image. The displayed image will be saved in the "Labeled" folder together with label files. Existing image and label files will be overwritten. Hint: it can also be done by using the mouse wheel.

data.name: button3.ToolTip
data.value:
Select the folder in which your training and valuation datasets will be saved and multiply your dataset by flipping and rotating the images.
Following subfolders will be created: train/ ├── images/ └── labels/ val/ ├── images/ └── labels/
These subfolders will be used when setting up the training model in NVIDIA DIGITS.

data.name: button2.ToolTip
data.value:
Select the folder where labeled images and label files will be stored. Subfolders //images and //label will be created.
If the folder contains labeled images they will be read and bounding boxes can be displayed and modified.
If you just want to edit existing bounding boxes select your /labeled/images/ folder as your unlabeled folder.
